Name: Nidhogg
Description:
Heavy melee unit. Good at using flames to burn enemy units. Can use Focused Flamethrower to continuously burn enemy target and Deflagration Bite. After advanced evolution, it can use Nibelungian Fire.

Can attack ground.

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Buries the unit underground. Burrowed units are unable to move or attack, but they cannot be seen without detection.
Root.Name: Burrow

Root.Tooltip: Mecha Ultralisk variant Nidhogg releases a bite on the target enemy unit after 1 second delay, causing 200 damage to the target unit (if the target has been ignited by Nidhogg's focused flamethrower, it will take 100% additional damage). After the bite, Nidhogg gains healing within 10 seconds and heals 20 health per second.
Root.Name: Deflagration Bite

Root.Tooltip: Nidhogg's head was equipped with a focused flamethrower, which allowed it to ignite fire on units in front of it when attacking, dealing 25 damage per second for 5 seconds.
Root.Name: Focused Flamethrower

Root.Tooltip: Nidhogg acquired Nibelungen Heating Equipment, can create intensive flames to burn nearby eneny ground units, dealing 15 damage per second. Meanwhile, Nidhogg will use Flames of Nibelungen to directly burn enemy units, deal 25 damage.
Root.Name: Flame of Nibelungen

Root.Tooltip: Mecha Ultralisk variant Nidhogg releases a bite on the target enemy unit after 1 second delay, causing 200 damage to the target unit (if the target has been ignited by Nidhogg's focused flamethrower, it will take 100% additional damage). After the bite, Nidhogg gains healing within 10 seconds and heals 20 health per second.
Root.Name: Deflagration Bite

Root.Tooltip: Make an advanced evolution, there is a 30% chance of evolution failure, causing Nidhogg to degenerate into the initial Mecha Ultralisk. After successful advanced evolution, Nidhogg will increase the power of Burst Bite and unlock the Nibelungian Fire.
Root.Name: Advanced Evolution
